                            <comment id="12613625" author="pi_song" created="Tue, 15 Jul 2008 14:41:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) In &quot;(long)age as age&quot; we treat &quot;as&quot; as type cast but in fact it is only used for altering the alias in this context&lt;br/&gt;
2) &quot;SUM(age)&quot; is aggregate of a flattened member which is a case we haven&apos;t handled yet in type checker (Normally we do like SUM(A.age) ).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think how we treat aggregates still can be improved to be cleaner.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
